notes:
Tested with a clean prefix (deleted old compatdata) and used old shader cache.
Decent FPS (mostly 60-90) on Xubuntu 18.04 with a GTX 1060 6GB (369.54) and normal-high settings. No compositor used (Window Manager Tweaks).
Launcher works fine without corefonts winetricks (installed ttf-mscorefonts-installer)

// Launch options: PULSE_LATENCY_MSEC=90 %command% -noChunkedDownload -DX11
// Fixes audio crackling with pulseaudio (see other fixed below), forces DirectX 11 and fixes (old) launcher download issues.

// FIX: Audio crackling with Asus Xonar DG (CMI8786 // snd_oxygen):
- Added the Steam launch option "PULSE_LATENCY_MSEC=90"
- Enabled "avoid-resampling" and disabled "realtime-scheduling" from /etc/pulse/daemon.conf

// In-game settings to improve performance and gameplay:
- Screen Type: Fullscreen (slightly better FPS and alt-tabbing works fine)
- Mouse Input Method: Windows (fixes the "180° mouse bug" in my case)
- Soft Shadows: NVIDIA PCSS
